OL,3,CNursery fined after mouse droppings
OL,4,Cfound in children's playrooms
OL,6,FFollowing an inspection in November
OL,7,F2023 the directors voluntarily agreed
OL,8,Fto close until the premises had been
OL,9,Fcleaned, and the nursery was issued
OL,10,Fwith a 0 rating ` meaning urgent
OL,11,Fimprovement was necessary.
OL,13,FA further inspection a few days later
OL,14,Ffound standards had improved and the
OL,15,Fnursery was allowed to reopen, but due
OL,16,Fto the seriousness of the issues
OL,17,Fdiscovered on the first visit legal
OL,18,Fproceedings were launched by Oldham
OL,19,FCouncil.
